You need:

typedef struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node* next;
} Node;

instead of:

struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node* next;
};

if you want to avoid typing struct every time. So now you can type Node* temp = (Node*)malloc(sizeof(Node));  instead.

